15/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Representatives of the Macedonian and the Kuwaiti foreign ministries signed an agreement on Monday (14 April), laying out the terms of the deployment of a Macedonian military unit and medical personnel to Kuwait, within the framework of the international post-war mission in Iraq. Parliament is expected to vote on the mission to Kuwait and Qatar at the end of April. The government also reiterated the readiness of Macedonian companies to participate in post-war reconstruction.
In other news Monday, Nebojsa Covic, Serbia's deputy prime minister and co-ordinator for southern Serbia and Kosovo, implied that unspecified individuals in Macedonia may be linked to the Zemun Clan, the organised crime group blamed for last month's assassination of late Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic. Covic named no names in his interview with Skopje's private TV Telma. (Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 15/04/03; MIA, Makfax - 14/04/03)
